Alan, tieuphilac, Chancewu, FTDS, pantrike, fallnavy, cenbo, FIFAWORLDCUP, Cloud, slamduk, coco_yuang, Ikon, luwenzhe, xiebin123xie, wetcat, nick_hopper, Sathudeptrai, shaoping, aivo, pengyu, weigui, mumax, eastmen, killer21st, scm2000, Andry, span, rainbowbill, Jasny_sokol, yzhnie, civsnail, jiujiumei, yyfcsd, smiling, shadewawa, gauss98, whte, amitabha.
We have learned lots of tactical methods which help black to attack,
or at least give benefits for black.
Until now, we have not discussed much about the difference of black and white.
The main differences of black and white:
black has always an extra stone, compared to whites.
Therefore black is more powerful by that.
That is why gomoku is black win.
Renju is a balanced game, because black has certain limitations.
Black is not allowed to use 3x3, 4x4, overline.
As my wish is to complete all the study of black side first,
so we will talk about forbidden moves from the aspect of blacks.
If you are black, you will need to worry about forbidden moves.
The worry begins from the simples question:
Is it a forbidden move or not.
In the rea game, there is no "red cross" telling you the answer.
In the real game you are on your own.

Now, the last 10 minutes of the lesson, we will focus on how does black manipulate with forbidden moves in renju games.
Sometimes, as black, we get to the situation where we have a 3x3.
But remember, 3x3 is bad only of the opponent can benefit from it.
Here of course, white could use the 3x3
But in most cases in renju game,
They may be annoying for black,
but they do not mean any direct danger.
Many beginners would think it is a crazy move.
But actually 3x3 is nothing special or nothing we should be worried of.
Now, there is one thing that many players do wrong tough:
having a 3x3, they will try to play it out,
so that there is no more 3x3 left.
But actually, we should keep the 3x3 open as long as possible, even we are black.
My last game in WC with Karlsson,
Black is tempted to resolve the 3x3,
but actually it is better to keep it alive, why?
To lure white to attack there and fail?

so, after such aggressive 12, it is necessary to take the means of resolving the 3x3, or blocking the aggression in other way.
As a general rule, black does not resolve the 3x3,
but simply blocks the white aggressive line that points towards 3x3
But there is one condition to keep in mind:
before black decided between resolving the 3x3 or blocking white line,
could white take any important point from black in the next move, if white simply chooses to defend,
so, before black plays to m8,
he has to check all the points of possible resolving of 3x3, such as:
If among these moves, there is an IMPORTANT point which black doesnt white to give to whites,
then black should resolve 3x3 first by taking that point
if black worries that white can go 14-k7 now,
and worries it is good point for white
then black may consider to take that point first
So, we need to check all the points first
if none of the resolving points is good for white
then black doesnt need to resolve the 3x3 at all and simply play 13-m8, understand?
the longer you keep 3x3 alive, the more powerful weapon it is for black.
But actually, if we analyse what we just learned,
Black will try to block white line without resolving 3x3 if possible.
We resolve 3x3 only if we have to!
so it meant black didnt have to resolve 3x3 into k6
which was just a waste of power.
And should white play any other move,
then black can always play k6 anytime later
and return to same position if he wants to
but having more different choices this way
For white, the k8 is the best defense now
And now black can go k8 if he wants to
but black has more freedom than just k6
while by resolving 3x3 early we are forced to get this:
So, please remember, the forbidden move is not always the enemy of blacks.
Black can manipulate with forbidden moves in highest level.
And let the forbidden moves support black plans in every way.
If you are not afraid of traps,
then you will not waste your power so easily.
we will start talking about white attacks, and especially the manipulation of forbidden moves from white's aspect.
